  saturated fat: 25 g
  carbohydrates: 60 g
  sugar: 7 g
  protein: 37 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 1000 mg
cuisine: Mexican
author: Michelle Doll Olson
servings: 2
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/pulled-pork-fiesta-bowls-5fe11a059050ec06d03e009e
time required: 20 minutes
---

In a #small pot{}, combine ¾ cup water and @butter{1%tbsp}. (For 4 servings, combine 1 1/2 cups water and 2 TBSP butter.) Bring to a boil, then stir in @Jasmine rice{1/2%cup}. Cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry all produce. Halve, peel, and thinly slice half the @yellow onion{1}(halved and thinly sliced) (whole onion for 4 servings); mince a few slices until you have @minced onion{2%tbsp} (3 TBSP for 4). Halve, core, and thinly slice @green bell pepper{1}(halved, cored, and thinly sliced) into strips. Dice @Roma tomato{1}(diced). Finely chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}(finely chopped). Quarter @lime{1}(quartered).

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add sliced onion and bell pepper. Cook, stirring, until just softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Tear @pulled pork{10%ounce} into smaller pieces. Add to pan with veggies along with another large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp}. Season with @fajita spice blend{1%tbsp}, @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until pork is warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1} and ½ cup water (1 cup for 4 servings). Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4). Simmer until saucy, ~{1-2%minutes}.

While pork simmers, in a #small bowl{}, combine tomato, minced onion, half the cilantro, juice from half the lime, salt, and pepper.

Fluff rice with a fork; season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between #bowls{}. Top with pork mixture, salsa, @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup}, and @sour cream{4%tbsp}. Sprinkle with remaining cilantro. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.

> We like to call these "fiesta bowls" because they've got all the best ingredients for
> making your taste buds boogie: tender pulled pork, warm spices, and a tangy tomato salsa.
> Plus, garnishes like Monterey Jack cheese, sour cream, and cilantro are guaranteed to keep
> the vibes lively. This dish can be on the table in as little as 20 minutes.